The paper deals with image analysis tasks using ConvLSTM models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also introduces a new framework for tree-structured image analysis, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) research.
